 <caption>
  <title>Confusion matrix for the IC
   <sub>50</sub> classifier.
  </title>
  <p>The accuracy (ACC) is defined as the sum of the true positive (TP) and true negative (TN): ACC = TP+TN; the balanced accuracy (BACC) is defined as the average between the true positive divided by total positive samples (P) and true negative divided by total negative (N) samples: BACC = (TP/P + TN/N)/2.</p>
